{
  "texts": [
    "We perform all experiments on the ESOL, FreeSolv, and BBBP datasets with 3 different scaffold splits.",
    "We did not use any pretraining for these experiments.",
    "We follow the same finetuning methodology as in Section Small hyperparameter budget.Importance of different sources of information in self-attention.",
    "The self-attention module in R-MAT incorporates three auxiliary sources of information: (1) distance information, (2) graph information (encoded using neighborhood order), and (3) bond features.",
    "In Table 5(a), we show the effect on the performance of ablating each of these elements."
  ]
}